              <h1>Agricultural Practices</h1>
				<p>There are several agricultural practices that are important for the success of a farm:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><b>Irrigation - </b>the process of supplying water to crops.</li>
					<li><b>Crop rotation - </b>the practice of growing different crops in the same field in a planned sequence.</li>
					<li><b>Fertilization - </b>the process of adding nutrients to the soil to promote plant growth.</li>
					<li><b>Pest control - </b>the practice of managing pests and diseases that can damage crops.</li>
					<li><b>Harvesting - </b>the process of gathering crops at the end of the growing season.</li>
				</ul>
       
        <h1>Types of Agriculture</h1>
				<p>There are several types of agriculture:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><b>Traditional agriculture - </b> involves using traditional methods of farming such as oxen and hand tools.</li>
					<li><b>Industrial agriculture - </b>involves large-scale farming using machinery and modern technologies.</li>
					<li><b>Organic agriculture - </b>involves farming without the use of synthetic fertilizers and pesticides.</li>
					<li><b>Sustainable agriculture - </b>involves using farming methods that conserve natural resources and promote environmental sustainability.</li>
				</ul>
       
