              <h1>Farming Equipments</h1>
              <p><b>Tractor:</b> A powerful vehicle with large rear wheels, used for pulling agricultural machinery and performing various farming tasks.<br>
               <b>Harvester:</b> A machine used to harvest crops, such as grain, by cutting, threshing, and cleaning.<br>
                <b>Plow:</b> A farm tool with a curved blade, used for cutting and turning over soil in preparation for planting.<br>
                <b>Seeder:</b> A machine used for sowing seeds in the soil.<br>
                <!-- <b>Cultivator:</b> A farm implement used for tilling and aerating soil to promote plant growth.<br> -->
                <!-- <b>Irrigation system:</b> A method of artificially applying water to crops or plants to help them grow.<br> -->
                <b>Combine:</b>A machine used for harvesting grain crops by cutting, threshing, and cleaning in one operation.<br>
                <b>Fertilizer spreader:</b> A machine used for evenly distributing fertilizers onto fields.<br>
                <b>Disc harrow: </b>A farm implement used for breaking up and smoothing soil after plowing, and before planting. 
                </p>
              
